Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lime{1}. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice
crosswise into half-moons. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @rice wine vinegar{2%teaspoon} (you'll
use the rest later), juice from half the lime, 1/2 tsp @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp
for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Stir in cucumber. Set aside to quick-pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large, preferably nonstick,
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce} and cook, stirring,
until just tender, ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and @pepper{pinch}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in same pan over medium-high
heat. Add @tofu{1}(crumbled); season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and remaining @rice wine vinegar{3%teaspoon}.
Bring to a simmer, then immediately turn off heat. Taste and season with
salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with @salt{pinch}. Stir in @water{1%tsp}
at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with saucy beef, carrots, pickled
cucumber (draining first), and cilantro. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Cut
remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side.